WEBVTT

00:10.053 --> 00:11.402
[seabirds chirping]

00:12.795 --> 00:15.928
BIANCA:
Come on, Lucca. You can take
at least a week off.

00:15.972 --> 00:18.627
I'm sending you a photo.

00:20.672 --> 00:22.239
There.

00:22.283 --> 00:24.285
What do you have in Chicago
to match that?

00:26.113 --> 00:27.766
Work.

00:27.810 --> 00:30.943
-I have work here.
-[scoffs] You can bring
your work here.

00:30.987 --> 00:32.989
Come on, I'm lonely.
It's just me here.

00:33.033 --> 00:34.991
[chuckles]:
Yeah, you and 30 staff.

00:35.035 --> 00:36.775
It's not the same.
I'll send the jet.

00:36.819 --> 00:39.126
You can be there
and back in 14 hours.

00:39.169 --> 00:41.650
The Herz divorce, upstairs.

00:41.693 --> 00:44.653
-Let's go.
-I got to go, Bianca.

00:44.696 --> 00:47.003
-Here we are.
-Okay.

00:47.047 --> 00:49.571
I'll say right up front,
this is not about my divorce.

00:49.614 --> 00:51.399
-Is it about your business?
-It's about my reputation

00:51.442 --> 00:53.401
-and it's about this firm.
-LUCCA: Which firm?

00:53.444 --> 00:55.664
-Reddick/Boseman or STR Laurie?-Aren't you all
the same these days?

00:55.707 --> 00:57.492
I keep bouncing
from one to the other.

00:58.536 --> 01:00.190
Yes. Tell us what you need.

01:01.452 --> 01:03.585
I saw this play last night,

01:03.628 --> 01:05.326
and for some reason,
it has my divorce in it.

01:05.369 --> 01:07.980
It has your divorce?
What does that mean?

01:08.024 --> 01:10.896
My divorce from last year?
The one you handled?

01:10.940 --> 01:12.289
-Uh, the one Lucca handled.
-[laughs]: Great.

01:12.333 --> 01:15.205
Circling the wagons
already, David? Noted.

01:15.249 --> 01:17.164
Either my $34 million
in legal fees

01:17.207 --> 01:18.643
matters to you or it doesn't.

01:18.687 --> 01:20.297
-It does.
-Then how the fuck

01:20.341 --> 01:22.517
did the specifics of my divorceend up in this play?

01:22.560 --> 01:24.867
Which parts of your divorce?

01:24.910 --> 01:26.869
My job, my ex-wife,
our reasons for divorcing,

01:26.912 --> 01:28.827
everything is in the play.

01:28.871 --> 01:31.482
Even some of the things
we said in the depos.

01:31.526 --> 01:32.701
They make me look
like an asshole.

01:32.744 --> 01:34.616
And what do you want to do?

01:34.659 --> 01:37.140
Seriously? You need to ask?
I want to sue.

01:37.184 --> 01:40.839
I want to Gawker these assholesoff the stage.

01:40.883 --> 01:42.711
Just give me a second.

01:58.422 --> 01:59.902
Yeah.

01:59.945 --> 02:02.687
I have to head upstairs
in a minute.

02:02.731 --> 02:04.733
-Um...
-What is it?

02:04.776 --> 02:06.126
Duncan Herz?

02:06.169 --> 02:07.910
The pizza king?

02:07.953 --> 02:10.391
[laughs]
Is he getting divorced again?

02:10.434 --> 02:12.393
No. He was satirized in a play,

02:12.436 --> 02:14.221
and now he wants
to sue for defamation.

02:14.264 --> 02:16.223
Tell him to let it go.

02:16.266 --> 02:19.400
Satire just disappearsif you don't give it any oxygen.

02:19.443 --> 02:22.142
-Everybody hates satire.
-Unfortunately,

02:22.185 --> 02:23.882
I recognized the playwright.

02:23.926 --> 02:26.233
He worked here last year,
as an associate.

02:26.276 --> 02:27.451
Who?

02:28.583 --> 02:29.845
Jumaane Jenkins.

02:29.888 --> 02:33.892
Oh, but his name
used to be Alan North.

02:33.936 --> 02:36.112
The one we fired for drug use.

02:36.156 --> 02:37.592
Yes.

02:38.767 --> 02:41.291
Damn.

02:41.335 --> 02:44.251
Does Herz know
he's an ex-associate?

02:44.294 --> 02:46.688
Not yet.

02:46.731 --> 02:48.124
He will sue us.

02:48.168 --> 02:50.474
-Yeah.
-Okay.

02:52.302 --> 02:53.999
Let me take this.

02:55.000 --> 02:56.437
Mr. Herz!

02:56.480 --> 02:59.266
-How are you?
-Adrian.

02:59.309 --> 03:00.528
-Yeah.
-Fine.

03:00.571 --> 03:02.138
-Good.
-What's going on?

03:02.182 --> 03:05.968
Uh, Lucca here filled me
in on the issue here,

03:06.011 --> 03:11.408
and I want to say, uh,I think we have some good news.

03:11.452 --> 03:14.977
We might have a path
to the lawsuit right here.

03:15.020 --> 03:17.284
So, uh, you give us a day,

03:17.327 --> 03:19.155
we'll take a look at the play,
and we'll see

03:19.199 --> 03:21.201
if any privileged information
was taken from our office.

03:21.244 --> 03:23.159
HERZ:
Good. I thought you were gonna

03:23.203 --> 03:25.335
-tell me to drop it.
-ADRIAN: Never. [chuckles]

03:25.379 --> 03:26.902
Not when it's this serious.

03:26.945 --> 03:29.165
Great. You'll keep me in touch?

03:29.209 --> 03:31.820
-Will do.
-All right.

03:33.952 --> 03:35.127
Thanks.

03:35.171 --> 03:37.129
Privileged information?

03:37.173 --> 03:39.306
What the fuck?
Was he a lawyer here?

03:39.349 --> 03:40.655
It's somebody we fired.

03:40.698 --> 03:43.266
Jesus, this place
is bush-league.

03:43.310 --> 03:44.920
David...

03:44.963 --> 03:46.617
[laughs]:
Fuck you.

03:46.661 --> 03:50.055
Take your opinion upstairs
and see what they say.

03:51.709 --> 03:55.017
[beeping]

03:55.060 --> 03:58.020
So, I don't understand.
The malware only attacks here?

03:58.063 --> 04:00.065
And only when I use
the firm's Wi-Fi.

04:01.415 --> 04:03.852
So someone here
is trying to freeze me out

04:03.895 --> 04:06.507
whenever I ask
"What is Memo 618?"

04:06.550 --> 04:09.249
-No, not here.
-Then where?

04:13.078 --> 04:16.386
Someone upstairs
is blocking my Wi-Fi access?

04:16.430 --> 04:19.346
Their head of litigation:
Bryan Kneef.

04:19.389 --> 04:22.697
-You're kidding. Why?
-My guess is because

04:22.740 --> 04:24.089
you're asking about
what you're asking about.

04:25.308 --> 04:28.529
Memo 618? He knows what it is?

04:28.572 --> 04:30.879
Uh...
[exhales]

04:32.402 --> 04:34.361
