08:09.750 --> 08:12.230
Man walks into a zoo.

08:12.274 --> 08:15.886
The only animal
in the entire zoo is a dog.

08:15.930 --> 08:17.932
It's a Shih Tzu.

08:19.150 --> 08:20.935
Want me to explain it to you?

08:20.978 --> 08:22.850
No, I get it.
I'm just not laughing.

08:22.893 --> 08:26.549
Caleb Garlin?
Do you have a minute?

08:26.593 --> 08:28.246
You, uh, worked with Bryan Kneef

08:28.290 --> 08:30.248
on a civil suit
that we can't find.

08:30.292 --> 08:32.076
JAY:
It was about six months ago.

08:32.120 --> 08:36.254
$895,000 in billable hours,
but no mention of the client.

08:36.298 --> 08:39.257
Uh, whatever you tell us, uh,
won't get back to Mr. Kneef.

08:39.301 --> 08:40.911
[scoffs]Oh, I don't care. He's a prick.

08:40.955 --> 08:42.565
Uh, Nola Garnett.

08:42.609 --> 08:44.436
The Tapas Group. Wrongful death.

08:44.480 --> 08:48.397
The docket number was, uh,
57-L-45-20.

08:48.440 --> 08:50.965
Wow. You have a good memory.

08:51.008 --> 08:53.663
[chuckles] I just don't trust
digital archiving.

08:53.707 --> 08:55.535
Um...

08:55.578 --> 08:58.973
I wouldn't leave it on there.

08:59.016 --> 09:04.065
The, uh, Tapas Group was being
sued by the wife of a prisoner

09:04.108 --> 09:05.762
who died while being transported

09:05.806 --> 09:07.938
in the back of one
of their private prison vans.

09:07.982 --> 09:11.289
-So, was there a settlement?
-No, just ended.

09:11.333 --> 09:12.943
