Are they really gonna smear
a black judge?

46:21.648 --> 46:24.129
Are you crazy?

46:26.566 --> 46:28.568
Of course they will.

46:33.442 --> 46:35.793
You're a conservative
black judge.

46:35.836 --> 46:38.404
You're not a dime a dozen.

46:38.447 --> 46:40.536
So what are you advising?

46:40.580 --> 46:42.277
Be an honest judge.

46:42.321 --> 46:46.325
Be what you always wanted to bewhen you got on the bench.

46:57.292 --> 46:59.947
Go to him.

46:59.991 --> 47:02.167
-No.
-[groans]

47:03.385 --> 47:05.823
He wants to fuckyou.

47:05.866 --> 47:07.912
He's never been
with a black woman before.

47:07.955 --> 47:10.915
-I'm his boss.
-Oh. So?

47:10.958 --> 47:12.960
He doesn't mind.

47:13.004 --> 47:15.093
He already said he doesn't mind.

47:15.136 --> 47:17.617
You know,
life is not like a play.

47:17.660 --> 47:19.837
There's no Human Resources
in a play.

47:19.880 --> 47:21.839
Invite him to a bar for a drink.

47:21.882 --> 47:24.145
Say you want to get
some work done there.

47:24.189 --> 47:26.452
Or... just go by the door,

47:26.495 --> 47:28.584
say you're heading out.

47:28.628 --> 47:30.978
I betcha he says,
"You want some company?"

47:31.022 --> 47:33.807
-Yeah, I bet he doesn't.
-Then do it.

47:33.851 --> 47:35.853
Don't you find him sexy?

47:37.680 --> 47:38.986
♪ White boys♪

47:39.030 --> 47:41.859
♪ Are so pretty♪

47:41.902 --> 47:43.773
♪ Skin as smooth♪

47:43.817 --> 47:45.688
-♪ As milk♪
-[mutters]

47:45.732 --> 47:49.344
♪ White boys are so pre-et-ty♪

47:49.388 --> 47:51.520
-Shh.
-♪ Hair like Chinese silk.♪

47:51.564 --> 47:53.522
There you go.
Grab your coat.

47:53.566 --> 47:55.350
Hey.

47:55.394 --> 47:57.178
I'm heading out.

47:57.222 --> 47:59.224
-How's it going?
-Going good. [chuckles]

47:59.267 --> 48:00.703
Yeah.

48:00.747 --> 48:02.053
You want some company?

48:04.751 --> 48:07.536
Uh, no, I'm fine.

48:08.886 --> 48:09.887
See you tomorrow.

48:09.930 --> 48:11.845
-Okay. Take care.
-Hmm.

48:11.889 --> 48:13.325
-[loud banging]
-Liz!

48:13.368 --> 48:14.892
Liz!

48:19.418 --> 48:22.856
♪ White boys are so groovy♪

48:22.900 --> 48:25.990
♪ White boys are so tough♪

48:26.033 --> 48:29.863
♪ Every time
they're nea-ear-ear me♪

48:29.907 --> 48:31.909
♪ I just can't get enough.♪

48:36.609 --> 48:38.393
Oh, God help me.

48:38.437 --> 48:40.178
I have just one witness
to depose.

48:40.221 --> 48:42.397
Great.

48:42.441 --> 48:43.703
Who?

48:43.746 --> 48:44.922
You.

48:46.967 --> 48:48.926
Sure.

48:48.969 --> 48:51.058
Take one last crack at me.

48:51.102 --> 48:53.582
It's your money.
[chuckles]

48:53.626 --> 48:55.367
JUMAANE:
Please state your name
and occupation for the record.

48:55.410 --> 48:57.108
Adrian Boseman,

48:57.151 --> 48:59.023
-partner and attorney.
-Mr. Boseman,

48:59.066 --> 49:01.590
after I offered to make changesto the play

49:01.634 --> 49:04.767
to satisfy Mr. Herz,
how did you advise him?

49:04.811 --> 49:07.118
I think that would fall clearlyunder the heading

49:07.161 --> 49:09.076
of privileged communication.

49:09.120 --> 49:11.426
-LIZ: Mm.
-JUMAANE: Given that
I was willing

49:11.470 --> 49:15.604
to change whatever traits he
found offensive, I'm wondering

49:15.648 --> 49:17.867
-what impeded the settlement.
-The remedy that you proposed

49:17.911 --> 49:21.871
was obviously insufficient
to undo the harm you caused.

49:21.915 --> 49:23.786
To whom, Adrian?

49:23.830 --> 49:25.614
-To our client.
-Is it possible

49:25.658 --> 49:28.313
that the harm,
as you perceived it,

49:28.356 --> 49:31.098
wasn't to your client
but to yourself?

49:31.142 --> 49:32.795
ADRIAN:
It's possible.

49:32.839 --> 49:34.972
-It just isn't true.
-Is it possible

49:35.015 --> 49:38.453
you've been using your client asa means of silencing my voice?

49:38.497 --> 49:40.455
LIZ:
I'm gonna object
to that question.

49:40.499 --> 49:42.805
You know,
you really give yourself...

49:42.849 --> 49:45.243
far too much credit, son.

49:45.286 --> 49:47.723
Your voice isn't that important.

49:47.767 --> 49:51.771
Mr. Herz, this firm is using youto advance their cause.

49:51.814 --> 49:53.773
-Please do not speak
to our client.
-Think about it.

49:53.816 --> 49:55.166
I'm giving you what you want.

49:55.209 --> 49:57.995
If they want something more,
let them sue.

49:58.038 --> 49:59.431
That is a lie.

49:59.474 --> 50:01.868
Let's... let's take a break.

50:06.046 --> 50:08.962
♪

50:13.314 --> 50:14.837
Hey.

50:14.881 --> 50:16.578
Hi.

50:19.059 --> 50:21.148
-Herz wants out?
-Yeah.

50:21.192 --> 50:22.236
Looks like it.

50:27.415 --> 50:28.895
[sighs]

50:30.201 --> 50:31.854
Look, I, um...

50:31.898 --> 50:34.161
you know,
I-I don't want us to feel...

50:34.205 --> 50:36.033
uh, I don't know, uncomfortable,

50:36.076 --> 50:38.339
-so I'll just say it.-Oh, uh, no, you don't have to.

50:38.383 --> 50:40.037
-We were drinking.
-Yeah, and,

50:40.080 --> 50:42.474
uh, I am your boss.

50:42.517 --> 50:44.389
So, um...

50:44.432 --> 50:46.391
we're good together?

50:46.434 --> 50:48.393
G-Good?

50:48.436 --> 50:50.699
[chuckles]
I mean, we're cool?

50:50.743 --> 50:52.049
Oh, yeah.

50:52.092 --> 50:53.572
Yeah, we're cool.
[chuckles nervously]

50:53.615 --> 50:54.877
-Okay.
-Yeah.

50:54.921 --> 50:57.184
Oh, that wasn't awkward at all.

50:57.228 --> 50:59.012
[both laugh]

51:00.231 --> 51:01.797
I'll see you tomorrow.

51:01.841 --> 51:03.973
Tomorrow.

51:04.017 --> 51:06.367
[door opens]

51:06.411 --> 51:08.413
[door closes]

51:10.241 --> 51:13.287
♪

51:20.338 --> 51:23.254
Greetings,
Lockhart the Lionhearted.

51:23.297 --> 51:24.820
Hello, Gabe.

51:24.864 --> 51:27.432
Um... we don't have
a deposition today.

51:27.475 --> 51:30.043
We don't have a deposition
at all anymore.

51:30.087 --> 51:32.480
Nola Garnett
dropped her suit against me.

51:32.524 --> 51:33.481
-What?
-Mm-hmm.

51:33.525 --> 51:34.830
-When?
-This morning.

51:34.874 --> 51:37.311
The Tapas Fund settled
her lawsuit.

51:37.355 --> 51:39.052
A million eight.

51:40.227 --> 51:42.664
And I am on board
for a third of that.

51:42.708 --> 51:44.144
They settled?

51:44.188 --> 51:46.668
Yes, and, Diane, I...
I wanted to thank you.

51:46.712 --> 51:48.757
I could've cut you a check,

51:48.801 --> 51:50.019
but, as they say,

51:50.063 --> 51:52.500
"Who steals my purse
steals trash."

51:52.544 --> 51:53.849
So...

51:53.893 --> 51:55.851
I wanted to do something...

51:55.895 --> 51:57.853
a little bit more, uh...

51:57.897 --> 51:59.551
personal.

52:01.205 --> 52:02.945
[squawks softly]

52:05.252 --> 52:07.428
[chuckles]:
Gabe, I-I...

52:07.472 --> 52:11.519
I don't know anything
about taking care of a bird.

52:11.563 --> 52:13.695
It's no big deal.
Fresh fruit twice a day

52:13.739 --> 52:15.784
and a steady supply of toys

52:15.828 --> 52:17.482
so it doesn't get bored.

52:17.525 --> 52:19.048
I love you, Diane.

52:19.092 --> 52:21.703
You... are... the best.

52:21.747 --> 52:24.010
-[bangs cage]
-[gasps, chuckles]

52:24.053 --> 52:26.273
It's okay.
You'll be fine.

52:27.274 --> 52:29.581
[car horn beeping]

52:36.414 --> 52:37.850
Hello?

52:39.112 --> 52:40.679
Hello.

52:42.898 --> 52:44.944
-You looking for me?
-No.

52:46.946 --> 52:49.078
I've already found you.

52:49.122 --> 52:51.255
Handsome set of dueling pistols.

52:51.298 --> 52:54.388
I'm guessing English,
mid-19th century?

52:54.432 --> 52:56.564
Who are you?

52:56.608 --> 52:58.871
[chuckles]
I won't keep you a minute.

52:58.914 --> 53:01.526
We think you should have a chatwith your wife.

53:01.569 --> 53:03.528
Beatrice?

53:03.571 --> 53:04.920
Your wife's seeking
to undermine policy.

53:04.964 --> 53:07.923
If you don't handle it, we will.

53:07.967 --> 53:09.838
Who are you?

53:09.882 --> 53:11.579
A visitor.

53:18.804 --> 53:20.501
Uh, this is Kurt McVeigh.

53:20.545 --> 53:23.765
I've got a strange man
in my office, TR-768.

53:23.809 --> 53:25.245
Can you send security?

53:25.289 --> 53:27.247
You might emphasize to your wife

53:27.291 --> 53:28.901
she's not a government employee,

53:28.944 --> 53:30.946
so she's not covered
by whistleblower protection.

53:30.990 --> 53:33.732
You, on the other hand, serve
at the will of the president.

53:33.775 --> 53:36.038
-Get the fuck out of here.
-[mumbles]

53:38.127 --> 53:40.129
♪

53:46.223 --> 53:48.703
How was he able
to get into your office?

53:48.747 --> 53:50.792
[sighs]
I don't know.

53:50.836 --> 53:54.143
I checked with security--
they never let him in.

53:54.187 --> 53:56.450
And he didn't say
where he was from?

53:56.494 --> 53:57.669
No.

54:02.021 --> 54:03.457
[Kurt sighs]

54:05.024 --> 54:07.287
You're worried.

54:07.331 --> 54:09.985
Well...

54:10.029 --> 54:12.292
my only regret from last year

54:12.336 --> 54:14.990
was not taking the threat to youmore seriously.

54:15.034 --> 54:16.731
Oh...

54:16.775 --> 54:18.733
That wouldn't have made
any difference.

54:18.777 --> 54:20.648
Well, you could have
stopped working

54:20.692 --> 54:22.824
with your political nuts.

54:24.652 --> 54:26.306
This is different.

54:26.350 --> 54:28.177
This...

54:28.221 --> 54:30.528
this isn't about politics.

54:36.882 --> 54:38.318
I just...

54:38.362 --> 54:40.799
don't...
[sighs]

54:43.105 --> 54:45.107
-What?
-[sighs]

54:46.631 --> 54:48.502
What?

54:48.546 --> 54:50.852
I don't want to lose you.

54:56.249 --> 54:58.338
I don't want to be lost.

55:06.259 --> 55:08.217
I'll drop it.

55:19.098 --> 55:20.360
[Diane moans]

55:21.753 --> 55:23.537
-Wait.
-What?

55:23.581 --> 55:25.060
Wait.

55:27.149 --> 55:28.934
[whispers]:
Wait.

55:30.936 --> 55:32.590
[door closes]

55:44.341 --> 55:46.212
What are you doing?

55:46.255 --> 55:48.780
Just give me one more minute.

55:54.786 --> 55:57.092
[door opens]

55:57.136 --> 55:59.138
♪

56:03.621 --> 56:06.275
-[breathily]: Howdy.
-[chuckles]

56:06.319 --> 56:07.973
Wow.

56:09.191 --> 56:10.628
Yep.

56:13.457 --> 56:16.764
You just lie back there, cowboy.

56:19.898 --> 56:21.900
♪

56:24.990 --> 56:26.644
Are you ready?

56:27.993 --> 56:30.909
Let's ride, Hoss.

